      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "OCEAN GOLD (1) ran well two back scoring a Bottom Up - Grade 6 win in 22.24 then out of the placings at Ballarat latest but returns to a course where she has performed well. Better than last run and makes appeal this time. ASTON FINNISS (2) has a strong winning strike-rate here with two wins and a placing from five tries. Missed the frame latest (23.21) when eighth over 390m at Ballarat in a Grade 5 H NP. Can feature in the finish. COLLECTIVE KAOS (3) is a capable type and proved too classy last time to win by 1.1 lengths at this track in a handy 22.88 beating Bismuth. Has performed well from this box with a win and three minor placings to his name from four starts. Sure to measure up. ASTON NIJINSKY (8) is in the mix despite finishing out of the placings here last start.",
